	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If your game exept SRAM, and runs on a SLROM board without SRAM (typically if is was something like SAROM, SJROM or SKROM), it is normal that it crashes. As long as you don't tell us the name of the game in question or if you don't verify it yourself on the board table (google something like "boardtable+SLROM"), we will be able to do nothing to help you.
<br />All SLROM boards are wired the same way, so I assume your game isn't compatible with the SLROM board.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
